<br>
I do not have my epic yet, and I am really torn between wanting pets better than the epic and not wanting to do such a nasty, long quest for something I basiclly will only use as a stat item. Am currently level 60, and one item away from getting my epic (staff of elemental mastery: earth). I'll likely get level 61 before finishing my epic. As nice as it'd be to have the post 61 pets being better than the epic, it doesn't seem appealing to have all the work I have done to date on my epic become moot.<br>
<br>
As for other epics, I have yet to see any caster epic become useless. Shaman and druids get a mana-free dot, this never becomes useless. Clerics get their best res, mana-free, again,  never useless even if they only wield the epic to do resses. Chanters get mana-free haste, invaluable when hasting raids, or fast pulling xp groups. It might not give as much haste as the highest level castable haste, the fact that SoS will haste cap most folks anyways and is mana-free more than makes up for it. I think only necro's are the only caster that is really unhappy with their epic, but I don't know why (seems good to me, guess a necro would need explain why they do not like it). In a nutshell, there's no real precedent for our epic effect becoming obsolete. People who say this are comparing to melee epics, and that's an apples and oranges comparison. (Not to mention melee's have had upgrades past epic's for some time, casters have not)<br>
